# Versioning

{{ display_name }} follows [Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html). Version numbers are `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`:

- **MAJOR** — breaking change to the public API
- **MINOR** — new functionality, backwards compatible
- **PATCH** — bug fixes, backwards compatible

v1.0.0 is the initial public release.

## What counts as the public API

A major bump is required when any of the following change in a breaking way:

### Runtime contract
- **Dynamic query URL grammar** — operators, identifier rules, literal syntax, and the set of reserved `$`-prefixed query parameters
- **Response envelope** — the JSON shape returned by dynamic endpoints and custom queries (`name`, `elements`, `links`)
- **HTTP status codes** — the code returned for a given condition (400 / 401 / 403 / 404 / 503 / 200)
- **Error body shape** — the top-level keys of error responses (`error`, message / title nesting)
- **`ERROR_DETAIL=safe` codes** — the stable failure-class strings: `db.bad_credentials`, `db.connection_refused`, `db.permission_denied`, `db.timeout`, `db.query_failed`. Renaming or removing one is breaking. Adding a new code is not (clients must treat unknown codes as `db.query_failed`-equivalent). The `verbose`-mode body — raw driver text — is **not** part of the contract.

### Configuration contract
- **Environment variables** — names and meanings of documented env vars (`CONFIG__SOURCE`, `AUTH__MODE`, `ALLOWLIST__MODE`, `OPENAPI__VISIBILITY`, `READINESS_TIMEOUT_MS`, `ERROR_DETAIL`, `MAX_PAGE_SIZE`, each variant's connection vars, etc.)
- **Default values** — a change that alters behavior for a config left unset

### Operator contract
- **Custom-query YAML format** — the schema of YAML files under `queries/` and `validation/`
- **Docker image contract** — exposed ports, entrypoint, required env vars

### Non-breaking additions allowed without a major bump
- New `$`-prefixed query parameters (existing ones unchanged)
- New env vars with defaults that preserve existing behavior
- New response envelope fields (consumers must ignore unknown fields)
- New endpoints
- New variant adapters

---

## What is NOT public API

These are internal. They may change in any version bump without notice:

- `core` module layout, class names, function signatures
- `DatabaseError` and other exception classes (internal contract between variants and core)
- DDL cache internal representation
- Log format details beyond the documented fields (`timestamp`, `level`, `logger`, `message`, `database`)
- Per-variant `db.py` function signatures
- Test fixtures and helpers
- Anything under `core/core/` not documented as public

If you import from `core` in your own code, you're on the internal side — expect breakage between minor versions.

---

## Version source of truth

- **Authoritative:** git tags on `main` (`v1.0.0`, `v1.1.0`, etc.)
- `core/pyproject.toml` — kept in sync with the highest tag
- Docker image tags — match the git tag

## Docker image tag convention

Images are published to GHCR at `ghcr.io/baelfur/{{ app_name }}-{variant}:{tag}`.

The tag is `<version-or-rolling><base-suffix>` where the base suffix is empty for the default `python:3.12-slim` runtime, `-distroless` for `gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12`, and `-dhi` for the Docker Hardened Image (`dhi/python:3.12`). The DHI tags only publish when the repo has Docker Hub auth configured (operator-side decision; see `release.yml`).

| Tag | Mutability | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `:X.Y.Z` | immutable | production — pin to a specific version (default slim runtime) |
| `:latest` | moves on stable release | local experimentation; pre-releases (`-rc.1`, `-beta.2`) do **not** update `:latest` |
| `:main` | moves on every merge to main | CI against the unreleased tip. Single-arch (linux/amd64) only. |
| `:X.Y.Z-distroless` | immutable | production with `gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12` runtime — minimal CVE surface, no shell at runtime, free anonymous pulls |
| `:distroless` | moves on stable release | rolling distroless tag, mirrors `:latest` |
| `:main-distroless` | moves on every merge to main | CI consumers who want bleeding-edge distroless |
| `:X.Y.Z-dhi` | immutable | production with Docker Hardened Image runtime — vendor-curated hardening (requires Docker Hub subscription with DHI entitlement to pull) |
| `:dhi` | moves on stable release | rolling DHI tag, mirrors `:latest` |
| `:main-dhi` | moves on every merge to main | CI consumers who want bleeding-edge DHI |

Stable release images are multi-arch (`linux/amd64` + `linux/arm64`) for all bases. `:main*` rolling tags are single-arch (linux/amd64) to keep the per-merge build loop fast.

**Picking a tag**: most operators want `:X.Y.Z` (default slim, anyone can pull). Pick `:X.Y.Z-distroless` when org-policy requires a hardened runtime and you want a free option. Pick `:X.Y.Z-dhi` when you have a Docker Hub DHI entitlement and prefer vendor-curated hardening over Google's distroless.

